I"g<p>When <a href="/vmware-esxi-upgrade-6-5-0-6-7-0/">upgrading to <em>ESXi 6.7.0</em></a> this error occured:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>[InstallationError]<br />
[Errno 28] No space left on device<br />
      vibs = VMware_locker_tools-light_10.2.0.7253323-8169922<br />
Please refer to the log file for more details.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>It can be fixed by manually installing the <em>VMware_locker_tools-light_10.2.0.7253323-8169922</em> VIB:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">cd</span> /tmp
wget http://hostupdate.vmware.com/software/VUM/PRODUCTION/main/esx/vmw/vib20/tools-light/VMware_locker_tools-light_10.2.0.7253323-8169922.vib
esxcli software vib <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="nt">-f</span> <span class="nt">-v</span> /tmp/VMware_locker_tools-light_10.2.0.7253323-8169922.vib
</code></pre></div></div>

